criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients presenting with stable or unstable CAD eligible for PCI (according to the
             international guidelines) because of diffuse CAD involving segments suitable for a
             hybrid approach;

          -  Signed Patient Informed Consent/Data Release Form

        Exclusion Criteria:

          1. Age <18 years;

          2. Cardiogenic shock;

          3. Pregnancy or breastfeeding;

          4. Infarct-artery max diameter (within planned device deployment segment) <2.0 or >5.0
             mm;

          5. Comorbidities with life expectancy <6 months;

          6. Severe calcification or/tortuosity proximally or at the DCB target segment;
